rth region $\\sim0.08$ Myr ago and it never had a perihelion distance\nsmaller than $\\sim0.7$ AU, while other CM2 meteorites with known orbits\napproached the Sun closer ($\\sim0.5$ AU) and were heated to at least 100 K\nhigher temperatures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Mar 2023 18:32:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 28 Mar 2023 15:35:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-29"}
