possibly a wedge, as determined via Monte Carlo simulations. This is further\nconfirmed by the X-ray polarization angle, which coincides with the direction\nof the extended radio emission in this source, supposed to match the disc axis.\nNGC4151 is the first AGN with an X-ray polarization measure for the corona,\nillustrating the capabilities of X-ray polarimetry and IXPE in unveiling its\ngeometry.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Mar 2023 13:18:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-09"}
